<TITLE> Sri Lanka U-19 get upper hand on first day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 7 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh Under-19 restricted their Sri Lankan counterparts to 329 all out on the first day of the second three-dayer at Colts Club ground Saturday. Sri Lanka Under-19 team were able to go beyond 300-mark after deciding to bat first, according to tigercricket.com, the official website of Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB). Skipper Mahmudul Hasan and Nasir Hossain grabbed three wickets each and Ashique chipped in with two wickets, it added. 
